result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy S. Rios was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Sex Offender-Fail/Provide Information, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 301.45(2)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to obtain and maintain full time employment.

Defendant to complete a Domestic Abuse Alternatives Program together with any follow through counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.  Defendant to comply with the Sex Offender Registration Program. DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.  Defendant to comply with any terms or conditions as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: Photos given to the Court by DA Blader at the July 7, 2014 Plea/sentencing hearing

14CF24 & 14CF66 Cases called @ 3:02 p.m. Defendant Timothy S. Rios in court with attorney Bryan D Keberlein.  Defendant Timothy S. Rios in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. As to 14CF24: The court entertains waiver of the preliminary hearing. The court accepts voluntary waiver of the preliminary hearing. Defendant bound over for trial. Information filed. Receipt admitted - Reading waived.  As to both cases: Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: 14CF24: Ct 1 - NC. 14CF66: Ct 1 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. 14CF24: Cts 2 & 3 - DRI. 14CF66: Ct 2 - DRI. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Atty Keberlein. No statement by the defendant. Court orders: 14CF24: S/W 3 years probation - Conditions: 4 months WCJ - Huber, No GT, 54 days CFTS - Sentence to commence forthwith, DAAP, defendant to comply with the Sex Offender Registration Program, Any other terms or conditions as deemed appropriate by supervising agent, defendant to maintain gainful employment, DNA sample and surcharge, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. 14CF66: S/W 1 year probation - Concurrent with 14CF24 - Conditions: Same conditions as 14CF24 with the exception of the jail time.
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 7, 2014 at 03:00 pm.
Status conference on June 10, 2014 at 09:45 am.
Status conference on April 30, 2014 at 02:00 pm.

No contact with children under the age of 18 unless they are in the immediate presence of a parent or guardian or if they are the defendant's own children. Defendant must be in compliance with all sex offender rules.
